# Frontend Environment Variables

# ============ API CONFIGURATION ============
# CRITICAL for production - Must point to your deployed backend
# Development: http://localhost:5000/api
# Production: https://your-backend-domain.com/api
VITE_API_URL=https://aurie.onrender.com/api

# ============ DEPLOYMENT NOTES ============
# 1. This file is for documentation only - DO NOT commit actual .env to git
# 2. In production, set VITE_API_URL to your actual backend URL
# 3. If VITE_API_URL is not set, will fallback to http://localhost:5000/api (development only)
# 4. Frontend communicates with backend through this URL for:
#    - User authentication (login/signup)
#    - Email OTP verification
#    - Phone verification via SMS
#    - Order management
#    - Payment processing

# ============ BUILD COMMANDS ============
# Development:
#   npm run dev
#
# Production build:
#   npm run build
#   (builds to frontend/dist/)
#
# The built files should be served by a web server or deployed to:
#   - Vercel
#   - Netlify
#   - AWS S3 + CloudFront
#   - Any static hosting
